## Clipper Magazine Coding Challenge

The Ruby program/script is written to accept standard input in the form of text, representing a rectangular map in which tildes (~) and carets (^) are used as symbols to represent water and land respectively. The program computes and outputs the area of the largest map present in the input.

#### Prerequisites 
- Install Ruby version 3 and above

#### Running the script
On a terminal or shell navigate to the project directory and run the below command
`ruby area.rb < sample.txt`